Heat broiler to high. Wash and dry all produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}. Slice @fully cooked chicken breasts{9%ounce} crosswise into strips.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{2%tablespoon} with @ranch dressing{1.5%ounce}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @coleslaw mix{4%ounce}, scallions, half the ranch sauce, and half the @Frank's RedHot® Original Seasoning Blend{7.2%g} (you'll use the rest in the next step). Toss until coated.

Place 1 1/2 TBSP @butter{1.5%tablespoon} in a second medium #microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until just melted, ~{20-30%seconds}. Stir in remaining Frank's RedHot® Original Seasoning until combined, then add chicken strips and toss until thoroughly coated. Microwave until warmed through, ~{1%minute}.

Spread @flour tortillas{6} out across a #baking sheet{} (divide between two #baking sheets{} for 4 servings). Sprinkle tortillas with @pepper jack cheese{1/2%cup}. Broil until cheese is just melted, ~{1%minute}.

> Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with chicken and slaw. Drizzle with remaining ranch sauce and serve.